The direct mode of primary elections has been dumped by the Nigerian Senate.  The Senate’s stand followed an amendment by the conference committee which recommended that “the direct primary mode of election be expunged.” The direct primary has been replaced with three options, including direct, indirect and consensus in clause 85 of the Electoral Act Amendment Bill, 2021. Details shortly…  Source Lagos - The Centre for Human and Socioeconomic Rights (CHSR) says the Senate has returned power to the people with the passage of electronic transmission of elections’ results. The Senate on Tuesday passed an amendment to the Electoral Act that allows the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) to determine the… In "Top Stories" The Senate has approved an amendment to the Electoral Act, which provides that political parties would henceforth use only the direct mode of primaries to elect candidates for elections. The Senate had earlier approved a provision in the Electoral Bill that allowed parties to use either direct or indirect mode… In "Politics" Will President Muhammadu Buhari sign the Electoral Act Amendment Bill recently passed by the National Assembly to allow the use of direct primaries to select candidates for the 2023 general elections or will he succumb to pressure from governors? The issue has been generating tension the political circles. TONY AKOWE… In "Politics"